result.execSummary:
The defendant Gabrielle Michelle Norwood was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Affidavit and order for payment of attorney fees and costs due from Milwaukee County signed.  Filed by:  CHRISTIAN THOMAS  $640.00

Defendant Gabrielle Michelle Norwood in court with attorney Christian Thomas.  Nate Kristian McClure appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Gabrielle Michelle Norwood appeared by video means with Attorney.
Case in court for status conference.  Defense counsel informed the Court that the defendant has completed CCW course. State placed offer on the record. 
Court ordered charge AMENDED to Disorderly Conduct, Co. Ord. 63.01 to which defendant pled no contest.
Court found defendant guilty and ordered defendant to pay a forfeiture of $50.00 including all costs by 09/19/2022 or civil judgment.

Defendant Gabrielle Michelle Norwood in court.  Navjot Singh Hira appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case recalled. Indigency Hearing held. 
Court found defendant is eligible for appointment of counsel by the court.  
Defendant agreed to repay Milwaukee County for the fees and expense paid by Milwaukee County. 
The court appointed Attorney Christian Thomas  to represent defendant  at County expense at the rate of $100.00 per hour.
Defendant repay the County at a rate of $30.00 Per Month. Repayment to begin 10/1/2022 Days after the conclusion of the case and on the first of each month until paid in full.  Defendant advised failure to pay will result in a Civil Judgment.  Status conference scheduled for July 19, 2022 at 09:00 am.
Defendant Gabrielle Michelle Norwood in court.  Navjot Singh Hira appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case called, case passed to allow defendant time to complete the indigency paperwork.

Defendant Gabrielle Michelle Norwood in court.  Thomas Hasle appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
HEARING HELD VIA ZOOM/ LIVE STREAMING THROUGH DACAST. Case in court for pre-trial conference. 
Defendant advises the Court she does not qualify for public defender appointment and cannot retain private counsel on her own. 
Court orders matter adjourned for indigency hearing.  Indigency hearing scheduled for May 27, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Court ordered no possession or use of any dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Gabrielle Michelle Norwood in court.  Mark O Thomson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant is advised that this case is assigned to Judge Dee, Branch 37. Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel. Defendant does not qualify for Public Defender representation. Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Case is adjourned for a Pretrial Conference in Branch 37.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for May 9, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Initial appearance on April 1, 2022 at 02:30 pm.
Court was not in session on 2/22/2022, due to the weather courts were closed. Court date for 2/22/2022 has been vacated. Case adjourned to 4/01/2022, at 2:30 p.m. in OCCR. Notice has been mailed.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 2/22/22 @ 2:30p
